ITV.Tour.de.France.2014.Stage.5.Live.PDTV.x264-NX

Wednesday 9th July 2014 ITV4
2pm to 5pm Live

Stage five has nine cobbled sections totalling over 15km which promises to be both exciting viewing, and dangerous riding. With a nod to Paris-Roubaix, the stage passes through iconic names like the Carrefour de l'Arbre and finishes in Arenberg. Hopefully the favourites can stay upright on this crucial stage, and not lose the Tour this early in the race. Presented by Gary Imlach with analysis from Chris Boardman, commentary by Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen with Ned Boulting the reporter at the roadside.
